  <answer><![CDATA[<p>Levi has a free ‘Kids Land’ in the resort centre for children of all ages, which includes a small ski lift, toboggan slope and weekly programme of outdoor activities. This is free of charge if supervised by a parent. Children from the age of 5 can join the pre-bookable, optional group ski school. Ylläs has an outdoor ski kindergarten on the Saaga side of the fell, which is free if supervised by a parent. Group ski school is available for children of 5 years and older. Saariselkä has a 1km toboggan run which is free for children if supervised by a parent. There is also a dedicated children’s ski slope. Group ski school is available for children from the age of 5 years.</p>]]></answer>
